@startuml MultiRegionTopology

title Multi-Region Disaster Recovery Topology - PSTA Platform

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor "Customer" as Customer

cloud "Route53\nDNS Failover" as Route53

frame "Primary Region\n(Active)" {

    node "Amazon EKS\nPrimary Cluster" as EKS1 {

        component "Risk Assessment" as Risk1
        component "Adaptive Authentication" as Auth1
        component "Transaction Decision" as Decision1
        component "Account Protection" as Protection1
        component "Audit Service" as Audit1
    }

    queue "AWS MSK\nPrimary Kafka Cluster" as Kafka1

    database "RDS PostgreSQL\nPrimary" as RDS1

    database "ElastiCache Redis\nPrimary" as Redis1

    storage "AWS Secrets Manager\nPrimary" as Secrets1
}

frame "Secondary Region\n(Warm Standby)" {

    node "Amazon EKS\nSecondary Cluster" as EKS2 {

        component "Risk Assessment" as Risk2
        component "Adaptive Authentication" as Auth2
        component "Transaction Decision" as Decision2
        component "Account Protection" as Protection2
        component "Audit Service" as Audit2
    }

    queue "AWS MSK\nSecondary Kafka Cluster" as Kafka2

    database "RDS PostgreSQL\nCross-Region Replica" as RDS2

    database "ElastiCache Redis\nStandby" as Redis2

    storage "AWS Secrets Manager\nReplica" as Secrets2
}

Customer --> Route53

Route53 --> EKS1 : Normal Operation

EKS1 --> Kafka1
EKS1 --> RDS1
EKS1 --> Redis1
EKS1 --> Secrets1

RDS1 --> RDS2 : Cross Region Replication

Kafka1 --> Kafka2 : Topic Replication

Secrets1 --> Secrets2 : Secret Replication

Redis1 --> Redis2 : Snapshot / Backup Sync

note right of Kafka1

Critical Topics

transaction-events
risk-events
authentication-events
account-events
audit-events

end note

note right of RDS2

RPO < 5 min

Cross Region Replica

Automatic Promotion

end note

note right of EKS2

Warm Standby

Infrastructure Ready

Containers Pre-Deployed

end note

cloud "Disaster Event" as Disaster

Disaster .. EKS1
Disaster .. Kafka1
Disaster .. RDS1

Route53 --> EKS2 : DNS Failover

note bottom

Disaster Recovery Flow

1. Detect Failure

2. Declare Disaster

3. Promote RDS Replica

4. Activate Secondary Kafka

5. Route53 Failover

6. Resume Operations

Target Objectives

RTO <= 15 min

RPO <= 5 min

end note

@enduml